The paper focuses on improving the loss function for CNNs used for image classification and face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.NE) and the achievement of good results in pattern recognition and object detection, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of various loss functions, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper specifically mentions face recognition, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
